Vite setup with React and deploy in github


https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/how-to-install-tailwindcss-in-react/

1. npm create vite@latest your-project-name -- --template react
2. cd food-app
3. npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
4. npx tailwindcss init -p
5. Open tailwind.config.cjs
6. "./index.html", "./src/**/*.{js,ts,jsx,tsx}",
7. open index.css
8. @tailwind base;
   @tailwind components;
   @tailwind utilities;
7. npm run dev
8. Open App.jsx
9. To verify tailwind is working add <h1 className="text-3xl font-bold underline text-center">Hello world!</h1>

Once you done with react project in local next we need to export our code from local to github, these are the steps to follow

1. Go to the local project main.
2. Open git bash comment ---> git -init

